00:36:20.950 --> 00:36:24.210
So we will continue to
follow the standards.

00:36:24.480 --> 00:36:27.420
Both Roberto and Rob were kind
enough to join us here and talk

00:36:27.420 --> 00:36:28.970
about the future as they see it.

00:36:29.260 --> 00:36:31.580
The good news is it's the
future as we see it as well.

00:36:31.620 --> 00:36:33.860
New codex for audio, new codex for video.

00:36:34.130 --> 00:36:36.920
The standards world is not
slowing down at any level.

00:36:37.060 --> 00:36:38.070
It's accelerating.

00:36:38.070 --> 00:36:40.820
When you go to these big trade
shows like IBC or any of the

00:36:40.840 --> 00:36:45.230
cell phone shows like CTIA,
it's standards everywhere.

00:36:45.440 --> 00:36:47.180
And if you want to see
the proprietary formats,

00:36:47.180 --> 00:36:48.880
you get to go to their
booth and look at them.

00:36:48.880 --> 00:36:51.150
And we think that that's just great.

00:36:51.150 --> 00:36:54.380
We think we backed the right horse,
if you will.

00:36:54.580 --> 00:36:58.470
But we put our money in the right place,
and now the dividends are coming back.

00:36:58.610 --> 00:37:00.800
And we're thrilled with
the progress we've made.

00:37:00.800 --> 00:37:02.730
So with that,
