Panther.

00:55:48.960 --> 00:55:54.610
So, the next section I want to
talk about is high def video.

00:55:54.610 --> 00:55:58.950
The domain of high definition
video is one of these areas that's

00:55:58.980 --> 00:56:00.740
kind of out on the bleeding edge.

00:56:00.740 --> 00:56:04.170
It's one of the coolest things
we've been involved with lately,

00:56:04.170 --> 00:56:06.320
and it's got some unique challenges.

00:56:06.320 --> 00:56:08.700
And I want to talk to
some of those challenges.

00:56:08.800 --> 00:56:11.960
The first thing is obviously just
take a little inventory of how

00:56:12.140 --> 00:56:15.200
big are we talking about here
when we talk about high def video.

00:56:15.350 --> 00:56:20.860
This is a representation of the clip
that you were looking at on the phone.

00:56:20.910 --> 00:56:24.800
So, this is sort of 3GP size, 176 by 144.

00:56:24.800 --> 00:56:28.240
This is sort of your standard
Internet type content,

00:56:28.280 --> 00:56:34.150
320 by 240, sort of traditional quarter
screen kind of stuff.

00:56:34.150 --> 00:56:40.210
Here's a full NTSC size, 720,
this is sort of typical DV type content.

00:56:40.460 --> 00:56:43.290
