00:57:00.800 --> 00:57:04.560
This is,
it can run anywhere from 95 to 155,

00:57:04.950 --> 00:57:09.170
160 megabytes a second,
depending on exactly how deep

00:57:09.170 --> 00:57:10.800
color you use and all that sort of.

00:57:10.800 --> 00:57:14.800
That's compared to the DV content
or the internet video content,

00:57:14.800 --> 00:57:17.620
which, you know,
it's like 2,000 times the

00:57:17.620 --> 00:57:19.760
size of the 3G data rates.

00:57:19.880 --> 00:57:23.500
It's just outrageously heavy duty stuff.

00:57:23.740 --> 00:57:28.050
Let me show you how that actually works,
though, and talk a little bit

00:57:28.050 --> 00:57:29.800
about those challenges.

00:57:29.800 --> 00:57:32.800
So,
let's switch over to the demo machine.

00:57:32.800 --> 00:57:34.680
So,
the first thing I'm going to do is I'm

00:57:34.680 --> 00:57:36.800
just going to pull up one of these files.

00:57:36.950 --> 00:57:40.780
So, this is a 10-bit uncompressed HD.

00:57:41.050 --> 00:57:44.590
Well, so the first problem I have is
